UML:TaggedValue.value:
1. The External System connects to the remote API. 2. The External System provides the user credentials to use for access. 3. The System authenticates the provided credentials. 4. The External System submits a search for objects of interest (experiments, samples, hybridizations, etc.) 5. The External System interrogates and navigates the object graph starting with one of the entities returned in the search, ultimately locating hybridization data of interest. 6. The External System requests the details of the design elements for the array design associated with the hybridization. 7. The External System requests a subset of the hybridization data for further analysis.
AFs:
- Unauthenticated access - File download - CQL search (as AF?) - Grid access - Authentication fails - Ad-hoc API usage (The Basic Flow illustrates the most common use of the API, but clients may invoke exposed methods in any order that is useful to the client).
SRs:
- Search interfaces - Remote Java and Grid interfaces

2. The System opens the project and indicates the ability to upload data to the project.

4. The System presents a dialogue that allows for multiple files to be selected from a local or networked location without restriction on the size or type (file extension independent) of files in addition to the ability to run the job in the foreground or background.

6. The System indicates the progress of each file as they are uploaded (see Special Requirements: Progress Meter) and the ability to cancel the upload at any point (see Alternate Flow: In Progress Cancellation).

7. The System indicates to the Data Owner when all files have made it and displays the list of files, their status (Uploading, Uploaded, Validating, Validated, Importing and Imported), the ability to select or deselect any one or all of the files and these actions: a. Return to Project b. Upload Files which returns the Data Owner to Step 4 c. Delete Files see Alternate Flow: Delete Files d. Validate see Validate Data Files Use Case e. Import see Import Data Files Use Case 8. The Data Owner selects to Return to Project that now displays the number of files uploaded.
